args:
When Cecile refuses to join his cause, Leif is
left searching for a way to escape Grams alone.
Yet he soon learns that in helping to hide him,
she has become a fugitive as well. After
rescuing her, the two once again take flight.
Fight? For the royal family? Me? Nuuuh-uh!\nNope! Nope, nope, nope, all of the nope.\nNooot happening, no way, no how, no sir.
Cecile? Are you well? My apologies for\nrequesting a thing so clearly upsetting.
I asked only because you were ever a\nknight of exceptional character.
Gyaaa! Stop! Stop that! Don't talk to me!\nQuit stabbing me with your pure words!
*pant* Oh man, I need a Manachew...
Cecile, are you certain you are all right?\nYou seem a bit unstable—and I question\nif that stone is helping or harming.
What, the Manachew? Yeah, about that...
...So after leaving the order, you fell into\na dismal state and began to rely more and\nmore on Manachew?

Pretty much, yeah. And I can normally hold
it together pretty well, but when folks go
off about chivalry or fealty or the like, I...
Well, you saw what happens.
I'm just overwhelmed with a wave of\nregret from my royal knight days—\nregret for how I couldn't save him.
I don't have the confidence to fight for any\ncause but my own anymore—or the right.\nHell, that's the whole reason I quit.
Which moment? When you chose to quit?\nDid something happen?
In any case, I can't help you. Can't fight for\nthe royals, and can't fight at your side.
Then why go out of your way to save me?
I just wanted to see if it really was\nyou they were chasing. That's all.
In that case, my apologies for making such\nan untoward request of you.
No. I'm the one who should be sorry...
(He hadn't changed at all. It was almost\nlike we'd never left the academy.)
(But compare that to me. There's no way I\ncan help anyone like I am now.)
(Guess I could've at least helped him get\nout of Grams. But knowing me, I'd just...)
Argh! Less thinking, more Manachew!\n...Oh no!
It's down to this tiny nub now.\nBetter go stock back up.
What the...? What do YOU want?
The White Sparrow captain. Where is he?
(Cecile has changed, though I suppose\ntime and circumstances will do that.)
(She was always the most loyal among us,\nand I'm certain Aurelius's death struck her\nthe hardest blow of all.)
I can't allow her to put herself through any\nmore on my behalf. If I am to slip this\nnoose, I must find a way to do it myself.
Right, you're clear. On your way!
Sheesh, the gatekeeps are really riled up\ntoday—that inspection took forever!
(Well, there goes any thought I had of\nslipping away disguised as a merchant.)
Why are you here? It's not your shift yet.
New orders from the cardinal: We're to\napprehend the female mercenary who\naided the Sparrow captain's escape.
They're leaving a skeleton crew on gate\nduty while everyone else joins the search.
(With the guards stretched thin, I should\nbe able to slip through. But I know the\nwoman they're talking about...)
Send squads to block every passage!\nBe careful, she's armed!
Don't let her use the terrain to her\nadvantage. Surround her, then close in!
(Ugh. I should've just left Leif to fend\nfor his own damn self.)
(Not that I could have done that...)
(Even I'm not so far gone as to sit by and\nwatch a friend get killed.)
Right then. If I jump down off this wall,\nI should be able to... Huh?!
Right! Looks like it's the alley for me!
Checkmate, sellsword. Now, tell us where\nthe White Sparrow captain is hiding!

I'm going to tell you what I've BEEN telling
you: I don't know where he is! Hell, you
and your goons already ransacked my
room. What else do you want?
More of that, eh? Well, let's see if a little\ntime in the Church's dungeon does\nanything to loosen your tongue.
Oh, of COURSE I run out of ammo now!
Forgive me for causing you so much\ntrouble, Cecile.
You idiot! Why did you come back for me?\nYou should've used the chance to run!
Last time I saw you, you were all fired up\nto get back to New Alberia!
But I am also not the sort of knight who\ncan stand idly by while a friend is killed.
Is there no end to them?
Leif, this way! Down the stairs and into\nthe sewers!
The waterways will take us clear of the\ncity. It's a maze down there, but I know the\nway—we'll definitely slip those guards.
As you predicted, Lord Harle, the Sparrow\nturned up to rescue that mercenary.
You never could resist a bit of bait, Leif...\nRight then. Post men to the specified\npositions—our quarry will arrive soon.
It's almost a shame I have to bring this\nlittle game of tag to an end...
